<section class="container hide" id="preview">
  <div class="span10 bottomBox">
  	<article class="row">
    	<%= image_tag "explore-notloggedin.png", :class => "span4" %>
    	<div class="sectionText span5">
	        <h2>Explore</h2>
	        <h3>Find an assortment of experiences on edtrips: kindergarden, college, day trips, weeks abroad, and everything in between. Searching for a professional company actively recruiting student travelers for travel abroad? Want to see what local treasures other teachers in surrounding areas have visited on their field trips? Want to share a great experience that students enjoyed? Show it off here.</h3>
    	</div>
    </article>
    <article class="row">
    	<div class="sectionText span6">
    		<h2>Engage</h2>        
	        <h3>Easily view trip details, sign up, pay a bill and manage both traveler applications and payments from a single trip page. With its own unique address, organizers use this page as a trip's site, share information and recruit travelers with one click. Find all the forms and itineraries right here as well.</h3>
    	</div>
    	<%= image_tag "trippage-teacherview.png", :class => "span4" %>
    </article>
    <article>
    	<div class="row">
    		<h2 class="span4">Create</h2>
    	</div>
    	<div class="row">
    		<h3 class="span7">Simple step-based trip creation make sure trip organizers require all the information they need.</h3>
    	</div>
    	<div class="row">
    		<%= image_tag "steps.png", :class => "span8 offset1" %>
    	</div>
    	<div class="row">
    		<h3 class="span7 offset3"><strong>Not just trip details.</strong> Set the traveler costs, structure payment schedules, upload or create forms, sync with contact lists, and set permissions to be as totally public or completely private.</h3>
    	</div>
    </article>
    <article class="row">
    	<div class="sectionText span6">
    		<h2>Manage</h2>        
	        <h3>Get into the nitty-gritty with a clear dashboard. Travelers pay for trips with credit card through edtrips, and organizers see the account balance held securely in escrow. Organizers have quick access to funds to pay for expenses when they need to. Forms stay with an account to make repeat trips easier than the one before.</h3>
    	</div>
    	<%= image_tag "mypage.png", :class => "span4" %>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>